Dr. '''Joseph Moreau''' is the [[Americans|American]] author of ''Schoolbook Nation'',<ref name="urlwww.historycooperative.org">{{cite web |url=http://www.historycooperative.org/journals/ahr/110.5/br_62.html |title=www.historycooperative.org |work= |accessdate=2010-11-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080905095127/http://www.historycooperative.org/journals/ahr/110.5/br_62.html |archivedate=2008-09-05 |df= }}</ref> a book detailing the conflict over the teaching of American history from the [[American Civil War|Civil War]] onward.<ref name="press.umich.edu">http://www.press.umich.edu/titleDetailDesc.do?id=17736</ref> He is currently a history teacher at [[Abraham Joshua Heschel School|Abraham Joshua Heschel High School]] in [[New York City]].

Moreau was born and raised in [[Dover, New Hampshire]]. He attended the [[University of New Hampshire]] for his undergraduate degree, and later received his Ph.D. in American Culture from the [[University of Michigan]].<ref>http://www.lsa.umich.edu/ac/graduate/currentstudents/dissertations</ref> Moreau formerly taught history at [[Trinity School (New York City)|Trinity High School]] in New York.<ref name="press.umich.edu"/>

