{{Infobox person | pre-nominals = | name = Julie Montagu | post-nominals = Viscountess Hinchingbrooke | image = <!-- filename only, no "File:" or "Image:" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] --> | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Julie Fisher | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1972|2|17}} | birth_place = [[Sugar Grove, Illinois]] | baptised = <!-- will not display if birth_date is entered --> | residence = [[Mapperton|Mapperton House]], [[Dorset]] | nationality = American | other_names = | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = [[Indiana University]] | occupation = Entrepreneur, yoga instructor | years_active = | known_for = | style = | home_town = | salary = | net_worth = <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source --> | television = ''[[Ladies of London]]'' | title = <!-- Formal/awarded/job title. The parameter |office= may be used as an alternative when the label is better rendered as "Office" (e.g. public office or appointments) --> | term = | spouse = Luke Montagu, Viscount Hinchingbrooke <small>(2005–)</small> | children = Four | parents = <!-- overrides mother and father parameters --> | mother = <!-- may be used (optionally with father parameter) in place of parents parameter (displays "Parent(s)" as label) --> | father = Thomas L. Fisher | relatives = [[John Montagu, 11th Earl of Sandwich]] <small>(father-in-law)</small> | family = | awards = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | module = | module2 = | module3 = | module4 = | module5 = | module6 = | footnotes = }} '''Julie Montagu''' (born February 17, 1972), [[Earl of Sandwich|Viscountess Hinchingbrooke]], is an American entrepreneur, yoga instructor, blogger, writer and reality television star.
==Early life== Julie Fisher was born on February 17, 1972 to Thomas Fisher,<ref>{{cite web |title=Hinchingbrooke, Viscount |url=http://www.ukwhoswho.com/view/10.1093/ww/9780199540884.001.0001/ww-9780199540884-e-20237 |publisher=Who's Who |accessdate=5 June 2018}}</ref> and was brought up in [[Sugar Grove, Illinois]], as one of five siblings. She went on to study [[computer science]] at [[Indiana University]]. Fisher moved to London to work for an internet based company, and was setting up a film school when she met Luke Montagu. She was a single mother at the time, and had assumed he was not interested in her. Three months after they began dating, she noticed that one of his [[payment card]]s had "Viscount Hinchingbrooke" written on it. Only then, did he explain that he was a member of the aristocracy and his father was the current [[Earl of Sandwich]]. A year after they first met, they married at [[Mapperton|Mapperton House]], [[Dorset]], the country estate of the Earl of Sandwich.<ref name="future">{{cite news |last1=Lambert |first1=Victoria |title=Meet Julie Montagu, future Countess of Sandwich and all-American guru of healthy living |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/family/parents-would-look-turn-backs/ |accessdate=5 June 2018 |work=Daily Telegraph |date=19 September 2017}}</ref>
==Career== When Luke Montagu suffered years of side effects from being removed from prescription medication by an addiction clinic (and was later awarded £1.3 million in compensation), Julie Montagu began running [[yoga]] classes in nearby church halls in order to bring some money into the household. She also started a blog, called the "Flexi Foodie" and wrote a successful cookbook,<ref name="future"/> ''Superfoods: The Flexible Approach to Eating More Superfoods & Superfoods Superfast''.<ref name="dorset">{{cite news |title=Luke and Julie Montagu: The duo taking up the reins at Mapperton |url=http://www.dorsetmagazine.co.uk/people/luke-and-julie-montagu-the-duo-taking-up-the-reins-at-mapperton-1-5110701 |accessdate=5 June 2018 |work=Dorset |date=28 November 2017}}</ref> She founded the charity Council for Evidence-Based Psychiatry after Luke's recovery, based on their experiences.<ref name="great">{{cite news |last1=Powell |first1=Rosalind |title=Great Estates: how the heir to the Earl of Sandwich runs 'the finest manor house in England' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/property/luxury/great-estates-heir-earl-sandwich-runs-finest-manor-house-england/ |accessdate=5 June 2018 |work=Daily Telegraph |date=4 December 2017}}</ref>
She was then offered a position on the [[reality television]] series ''[[Ladies of London]]'' as her husband was recovering. She later said of the series, "We thought long and hard before accepting as it offered financial support for a while. But it was not fun to do. I was expected to behave in a way I wasn’t, like an [[It girl]] or socialite, when I'm not. They edit you... You have to go along with things or you get fired. But you know it was a job. I was acting." She celebrated when it was cancelled after three seasons.<ref name="future"/> In 2016, the couple took over the running of the Mapperton Estate.<ref name="dorset"/>
The series brought financial stability which allowed the couple to invest further in the Mapperton Estate, turning an old stable block into a wedding venue. Julie Montagu has also opened her own school of yoga within the grounds, but continues to practice yoga elsewhere such as being the headline act at the Wanderlust yoga festival in [[Victoria Park, London|Victoria Park]], London.<ref name="future"/> During the lead up to the [[Wedding of Prince Harry and Meghan Markle]], Julie Montagu was interviewed on a number of occasions because she is an American who married into British aristocracy,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Relph |first1=Daniella |title=Meghan Markle and Prince Harry: A royal shake-up |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-42112647 |accessdate=5 June 2018 |work=BBC News |date=27 November 2017}}</ref> and was an on-site commentator on the wedding for the [[BBC]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Halleman |first1=Caroline |title=I'm an American Who Married into the British Aristocracy. Here's My Advice for Meghan Markle. |url=https://www.townandcountrymag.com/society/tradition/a19830489/julie-montagu-advice-meghan-markle/ |accessdate=5 June 2018 |work=Town & Country |date=16 April 2018}}</ref>
==Personal life== She is married to Luke Montagu, Viscount Hinchingbrooke, and has four children.<ref name="future"/> Two of those are from her first marriage, and two with Luke.<ref name="dorset"/> She supported her husband through his recovery from a dependency of prescription drugs and now campaigns for greater awareness of the issue.<ref name="future"/>
