[[File:Theodor Ludwig Wilhelm von Bischoff.jpg|right|thumb|Portrait of Theodor von Bischoff (ca. 1870)]] '''Theodor Ludwig Wilhelm von Bischoff''' (28 October 1807 in [[Hannover]] – 5 December 1882 in [[Munich]]) was a German physician and biologist.
== Biography == He lectured on [[pathological]] anatomy at [[University of Heidelberg|Heidelberg]] (1835-1843) and held professorships in [[anatomy]] and physiology at [[University of Giessen|Giessen]] (1843-1855) and [[University of Munich|Munich]], where he was appointed to the chair of anatomy and [[physiology]] in 1854.{{sfn|Wood|1907}} In 1843, Theodor von Bischoff was elected as member of the German Academy of Sciences.<ref>http://www.leopoldina.org/de/mitglieder/mitgliederverzeichnis/member/2024/</ref>
His most important contributions were made in [[embryology]] with a series of four exhaustive memoirs on the development of the mammalian [[ovum]]; published in 1842 (rabbit), 1845 (dog), 1852 ([[guinea pig]]), and 1854 ([[roe deer]]).<ref>{{harvnb|Driesch|1911|p=326}}, 2nd ¶ from end of page.</ref> His studies concerning animal metabolism by measuring [[urea]] were less successful, as was his research on the anatomy of skull and brain.
He was elected a foreign member of the [[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]] in 1878.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.dwc.knaw.nl/biografie/pmknaw/?pagetype=authorDetail&aId=PE00002630 |title=T.L.W. von Bischoff (1807 - 1882) |publisher=Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences |date= |accessdate=22 May 2016}}</ref>
== Selected works == * ''Beiträge zur Lehre von den Eyhüllen des menschlichen Fötus'', 1834 &ndash; Contributions to the study of the [[human fetus]]. * ''Entwickelungsgeschichte der Säugethiere und des Menschen'', 1842 &ndash; Developmental history of mammals and man. * ''Entwicklungsgeschichte des kaninchen-eies'', 1842 &ndash; Developmental history of the rabbit ovum. * ''Entwicklungsgeschichte des hunde-eies'', 1845 &ndash; Developmental history of the dog ovum. * ''Entwicklungsgeschichte des meerschweinchens'', 1852 &ndash; Developmental history of the guinea pig. * ''Entwicklungsgeschichte des Rehes'', 1854 &ndash; Developmental history of the roe deer. * ''Die Grosshirnwindungen des Menschen : mit Berücksichtigung ihrer Entwicklung bei dem Fötus und ihrer Anordnung bei den Affen'', 1868 &ndash; The cerebral convolutions of man. * ''Das Studium und die Ausübung der Medicin durch Frauen'', 1872 &ndash; The study and practice of medicine by women.<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n87-141161/ Most widely held works by Th. Ludw. Wilh Bischoff] WorldCat Identities</ref> [[File:Familiengrab Theodor Ludwig Wilhelm von Bischoff (1807-1882).jpg|thumb|228px|Grave of Theodor Bischoff at the Alten Südlichen Friedhof in Munich]]
